   "body" : "The RPC server is supposed to bind to all interfaces when the `-rpcbind=<addr>` option is not set (https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Running_Bitcoin). When running `bitcoin-qt.exe -server -rpcuser=u -rpcpassword=p` the server binds to `127.0.0.1`, though, and not to all interfaces. This causes the server to be unreachable from another machine. Looks like a bug.",
